@node Introduction "Introduction to MassDL"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

  @{b}MassDL@{ub} is a AREXX Web Browser plugin meant to make simpler many file
 downloads. Save locally links and/or images you select of an HTML
 document using a pattern and more options. You can either use Aweb or
 Go Fetch! to download files.

  Features:
   À Easy to use (GUI)
   À Use Aweb or Go Fetch! to download files
   À Default actions to choosen URL Patterns
   À Hold URLs to download later
   À Remember last options.
   À Frame support
   À Extensive settings.
   À Cooperative with other scripts.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements to MassDL"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

  MassDL requires:
   À AmigaOS - only tested on v3.x
   À AWeb - only tested on v3.3
   À bguirexx.library  v3.x+ and bgui.library for the GUI (1st one provided)
   À rexxdossupport.library (not included: ® reasons)
     on Aminet: util/rexx/rexxdossupport.lha
   À rexxsupport.library (provided)

  Optional:
   À Go Fetch! - only tested on v1.2

@endnode

@node Installation "Installation of MassDL"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

  Copy the Libs you need form "Libs/" to "Libs:".
  Copy the script (MassDL.awebrx) file to wherever you want and config
 AWeb to run it. Examples:

 Command: "RUN AWebPath:Plugins/MassDL.awebrx"
 Command: "RUN AWebPath:Plugins/MassDL.awebrx HOLD"
 Command: "RUN AWebPath:Plugins/MassDL.awebrx GETHOLD"
 Command: "RUN AWebPath:Plugins/MassDL.awebrx HOLD AWeb_port=AWEB.2"

  Also, "MassDL.rx_src" file is included for those who want to look
 to the code wich is a little difficult with "MassDL.awebrx". :)

@endnode

@node Configuration "Configuring default operations of MassDL"

 @{b}@{u}Configuration@{uu}@{ub}

  MassDL is configured by GUI. If there is no config file already
 built when you run MassDL a GUI with default settings will appear
 giving the chance to save them. You have to save a config to run
 MassDL.

  @{b}Main Options:@{ub}
   The actual files downloads can be passed to AWeb or either Go Fetch!.
  If you prefer Go Fetch select it here. If Go Fetch! is not running
  MassDL will try to run it with the supplied "Path + GoFetch! exe file",
  selected right after the checkbox.
   When file names to be saved that contain chars inadvisable for
  AmigaOS are found, MassDL can "let it be" or replace them.
  If "Inadvisable Chars" is NOT set it will replace those chars with a '_'.
  For now the chars are "%|()[]*`".
  Note: filenames will never contain "?#;<>:/", at least for now.

  @{b}Default Options:@{ub}
   Options that the GUI will open with, if no "Remember" action was
  choosen or the URL doesnt match any of the patterns in the URL List.
   For futher details about default options see @{"Usage" link Usage}.

  @{b}URL List:@{ub}
   Here you can set the Default URL Actions MassDL will take on listed
  URL Patterns. You can drag the entrys so you can order them as you
  prefer. For MassDL the order isn't important.
   If you choose to @{b}edit@{ub} the selected entry a new window will be opened.
  You can set the @{b}URL Pattern@{ub} using or not wildcards. For example:
   À "http://www.vegan.org/index.html"
   À "*www.nocompromise.org/alf/*"
   À "http://www.dummyurl.???/#?/index#?"
  Remember that "http://www.vegan.org/" is not the same as
  "http://www.vegan.org/*".
   MassDL will compare every URL Patterns so no entry will get any
  results that other does.
   The @{b}GetURL@{ub} button will copy and paste the current selected URL on
  AWeb. (You can choose new URLs and get back to MassDL and paste them.)
   If you choose to @{b}AutoDL@{ub} no GUI will be opened and Automatic Lech
  with selected options will begin. Use wiselly, there is no need to
  file trash your HD all over. :)
   If you select not to apply to all @{b}frames@{ub} and the URL pattern match
  a URL that contains frames, the Frame you select when running MassDL
  is expected to be the desired frame to take actions on. If no Frame
  is selected a rquester will pop up.
   All other options are described in @{"Usage" link Usage}.

  When you want to change configuration you must use the button on the main
 GUI.

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage of MassDL"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

  @{b}Command Line:@{ub}   MassDL.awebrx [HOLD/S|GETHOLD/S] [AWeb_port/K]

  All are optional and the order or letter case is not important. You may
 only use HOLD or GETHOLD with or without AWeb_port.
  HOLD - No GUI, only hold URLs to DL if any found and nothing else is
         done. Only usefull when used with "Auto DL" feature of
         "URL List config"
  GETHOLD - Only download holded files if any. No GUI.
  AWeb_port - Aweb AREXX port to use. Default port is the one of the selected
              window when script runs.

  @{b}GUI:@{ub}
   At the top-left there are options for Link DLs. Select the box to enable
  and use "->" to copy the pattern you choosed to the pattern for the
  images.
   At the top-right you can discover yourself. :)
   On the Bottom-Right there is a check box that
  will enable the options you made to be remembered next time you run the
  script. When the options are remembered it is by default already selected.
   This is useful if you repeat the same operation more than once. No
  need to set the same options, just press the box so that next time the
  options start the same.
   Save main document:
     You can choose to Save the displayed document, or documents if frames.
   Apply to Frames:
     If you selected a frame page you can choose to apply all options to
     all frames.

  @{b}Frames:@{ub}
   If you run MassDL on a frame page you can select the frame you want
  to refer to before you start the script. If you dont do so and MassDL
  detects no frames were selected neither "Apply to frames" option was
  selected on/if GUI, a request appears asking you either to select the
  frame in that momment, to apply to all frames or cancel the whole
  operation.

  @{b}Hold files:@{ub}
   In this feature MassDL holds (saves) the URLs you selected to
  filter, to download a next time. You can acumulate request after request.
   For now you cant delete already holded files so take than in
  consideration.
   If you use the GUI you can see on the bottom-left a status text saying
  if there are any holded files or not.

  @{b}Local Save method:@{ub}
   You can choose how do you want the file tree of your DLs to be saved.
  If "Direct Path" is selected all files will be saved under the SavePath
  you selected with no futher directory creation. If "1 URL Level Path"
  is choosen only a directory with the machine name of the URL is created
  and all files are saved there. If "All URL Levels Path" all directorys
  on the URL will also be created.
   For example:

      URL: "http://www.comssucks.yep/~user30/destroy/HowTo.html"
      SavePath selected: "Work:DL"

   Method 0 will save "Work:DL/HowTo.html"
   Method 1 will save "Work:DL/www.comssucks.yep/HowTo.html"
   Method 2 will save "Work:DL/www.comssucks.yep/user30/destroy/HowTo.html"

   @{u}Note:@{uu} Don't use URLs containing spaces not encoded like
  "http://www.comssucks.yep/How To.html". Instead, if possible, transform
  them in "http://www.comssucks.yep/How@{b}%20@{ub}To.html" like standard URLs
  should be.
  If no transformation is done before running MassDL an incorrect Save tree
  and file name can be produced.

  @{b}Possible 3rd party REXX script syncronization:@{ub}
   With the new command line options introduced in version 1.8, syncronization
 with other programs becomes easier using OS command lines.
   Besides this, MassDL issues an AREXX command on a specific message port
 when it is done. This way it can for example run in another process/thread
 and still be noticed when all its actions are done. This should also make
 easier to syncronize with other programs like AREXX scipts.
     AREXX port used: MASSDLAUX
     Command isued:   Status = "CONTINUE"

   Command is only issued if port is open, so you have to create one in your
 script, wait for the packet, close the port and so on.

@endnode

